cp.diachronicDesc: Corpora used to study changes in time using the Trends feature. Diachronic corpora contain time information about when a text was published or used.
cp.error-annotatedDesc: Corpora used to study errors produced by users of the language: typically learner's errors or translator's errors. The corpora contain error annotation giving details about the error, correction and type of error.

macrosDesc: To save concordance actions as a macro, first generate a concordance and apply filters, sorting, random sample, frequency or other actions. Then save the actions as a macro. Macros let you automate actions applied to a concordance. When they are saved as a macro, Sketch Engine will carry them out automatically. A saved macro can be selected on the concordance input form before each search or it can be selected permanently to be applied on all subsequent concordances.
